A survey revealed that people in Shanghai, especially in the 7-12 and 60-70 age groups, face a higher risk of obesity, with males more affected than females.
Improved lifestyles and poor eating habits contribute to this issue.
In Beijing, lack of exercise, excessive sleep, and high-fat, high-calorie diets lead to unwanted weight gain.
Experts warn of the health risks associated with obesity, including cardiovascular diseases and diabetes.
The government aims to reduce obesity rates by 2005, emphasizing the importance of promoting sensible lifestyles.
Additionally, hypnotism has shown success in treating obesity in Kuwait, where a large percentage of the population is affected
